article.headline: Northeastern 58, North Carolina-Wilmington 51
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Bennet Davis had 12 points, eight rebounds and seven blocks to lead Northeastern to a 58-51 win over UNC Wilmington on Saturday in the Colonial Athletic Association opener for both teams. Adrian Martinez scored 12 points and Bobby Kelly added 11 for the Huskies, who beat the defending CAA-champion Seahawks for the first time. After Jeff Horowitz tied it a 49 with 2:34 remaining, Northeastern (2-5, 1-0) went on a 9-0 run before Montez Downey made a layup with three seconds left. Manny Adako's layup with 2:18 left snapped the tie, and the Huskies made seven free throws in the closing minutes to put the game out of reach. Vladimir Kuljanin scored 20 points and Temi Soyebo added six assists and a career-high 16 rebounds for the Seahawks, who lost despite outrebounding the Huskies 49-31. Northeastern trailed 16-14 after 10 minutes, but outscored the Seahawks 15-6 the rest of the first half to take a 29-22 halftime lead. Kuljanin and Soyebo combined for 10 straight points to open the second half and give Wilmington (2-4, 0-1) a 32-29 lead. But Northeastern responded with a 6-0 spurt to make it a close game until taking over in the closing minutes. Northeastern scored 24 points off 18 Wilmington turnovers.
